2015}) (12... Nf6 13. Ng5 {- 11...Nf6 12 Bd3 Re8 13 Ng5}) 13. Bg5 $5 {Is a
very subtle idea.} (13. Bf4 $5 {is a recent attempt by Praggnanandhaa} Nf6 14.
Rde1 Rxe1+ (14... Ne4 $6 {sacrifices a pawn for a vague compensation} 15. Bxe4
dxe4 16. Rxe4 Be6 17. Qxd8 Raxd8 18. Be3 Bf8 19. b3 $14 {even though Black has
the bishop pair her compensation isn't readily visible. 1-0 (57)
Praggnanandhaa,R (2532)-Ju Wenjun (2580) Prague CZE 2019}) 15. Rxe1 Bd7 16. Ne5
$5 {this leads to interesting play.} (16. a4 $5 {is a move that only Lc0 could
suggest!}) (16. g3 Bf8 17. c4 h6 18. Ne5 Be6 19. Qe2 Qb6 20. cxd5 Nxd5 $11 {
1/2-1/2 (36) Cvak,R (2292)-Istomin,A (2157) ICCF email 2017}) 16... Be6 17. f3
Bd6 18. g4 Qc7 {/\Nd7} 19. Bh2 Re8 (19... Nd7 20. Nxd7 Bxd7 (20... Bxh2 {
looks dangerous after} 21. Nf6+ $1 gxf6 22. Qh6 f5 (22... Qg3 23. Bxh7+ Kh8 24.
Bd3+ Kg8 25. Rf1 {and White can play on with a draw in his pocket. Possible
