Nd7 9. O-O-O Nf6 10. Bd3 c5 {This is the main move.} 11. Bg5 {This appears to
be more precise as White can later choose whether he wants a rook on e1 or not.
} (11. Rhe1 Be6 12. Kb1 (12. Bg5 d5 13. Qf4 {- 11 Bg5 Be6 12 Qf4 d5 13 Rhe1})
12... Qa5 13. a3 $5 {an interesting novelty by Caruana, this time on the other
side of the barricades!} (13. c4 {didn't give Carlsen anything after} Qxd2 14.
